    • Method Detail

      • generateDownstream

        ReconciliationReport generateDownstream(Associative root,
                                        NavigationCriteria upnc,
                                        NavigationCriteria downnc,
                                        boolean doAutoCheckin)
                                 throws WTException
        API to allow you to start the downstream generation from a given root node. This API will directly start from the given node and execute the DiscrepancyType.ADDUSAGE logic. This is different and detectAndResolve(ReconciliationContext) that this API does not do any detection and assumes that caller knows that root is a added node where there is no parent or parent information is not relevant.
        Supported API: true

        Extendable: false
        Parameters:
        root - - the node from where to start the add template logic.
        upnc - - navigation criteria to navigate upstream structure. this is optional and if not provided we get a default nc.
        downnc - - navigation criteria to navigate downstream structure. this is optional and if not provided we get a default nc.
        doAutoCheckin - - tells if all checked out nodes on downstream structure should be checked-in or not.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        WTException

      • getDiscrepanciesFromJSON

        java.util.Collection<Discrepancy2> getDiscrepanciesFromJSON(ReconciliationContext context,
                                                            java.lang.String discrepancyJSONArray)
                                                     throws WTException
        Returns a collection of discrepancies by calling respective delegates for each discrepancy JSON. Expects input as JSONArray string.
        Supported API: true

        Extendable: false
        Parameters:
        context - - the context having information for navigation criteria and other common data
        discrepancyJSONArray - - the toString of JSONArray
        Returns:
        - collection of discrepancies having one entry for each discrepancy unless no delegate is found for some discrepancy. no order guarantee is provided.
        Throws:
        WTException

      • getJSONFromDiscrepancies

        java.lang.String getJSONFromDiscrepancies(ReconciliationContext context,
                                          java.util.Collection<Discrepancy2> discrepancies)
                                   throws WTException
        Returns a JSON array of discrepancies by calling respective delegates for each discrepancy
        Supported API: true

        Extendable: false
        Parameters:
        context - - the context having information for navigation criteria and other common data
        discrepancies - - the discrepancies which needs to be converted to JSON. each discrepancy will have one entry in the JSONArray string which is output. No order guarantee is provided but if input is List then it should be ideally in the same order.
        Returns:
        - toString of JSONArray
        Throws:
        WTException
